description: Yaks are long-haired bovids adapted to high-altitude environments in the Himalayas, used as pack animals and for milk meat.
They graze on alpine grasses and are well adapted to cold.
The yellowhammer is a small passerine with bright yellow plumage in parts of its range, commonly found in open countryside.
They feed on seeds and insects and nest in hedgerows and fields.
Yabbies are freshwater crayfish native to Australia that live in rivers, lakes and wetlands and feed on detritus and small animals.
They are important in freshwater food webs and are fished locally.
The common yellowthroat is a small New World warbler with distinctive black mask in males, frequent in marshy and shrubby habitats.
They feed on insects and spiders.
The yapok or water opossum is a semiaquatic marsupial from the Americas that forages in freshwater for fish and invertebrates.
It is adapted to aquatic life with water-repellent fur and webbed hind feet.
